homepage toney research lab home contact people links outreach research publications news and events postdoc opportunities ssrl materials sciences division welcome to the toney research group at the stanford synchrotron lightsource ssrl part of the slac national accelerator laboratory our research is focused on structural characterization of materials used for energy conversion and storage and for information processing please see the research area for examples and more details much of our work is carried out in collaboration with faculty and staff members at other institutions many of these are local but some are spread worldwide most of our structure based studies are done on beam lines at ssrl
